It would be much easier to understand if we represent the empty list with an actually empty list rather than null.
I have checked the SqlExecuteMessageTask code. It would simplify the code there also.
Instead of
 if (parameters.parameters != null && !parameters.parameters.isEmpty()) {
                for (Data param : parameters.parameters) {
                    query.addParameter(serializationService.toObject(param));
                }
            }

the following will suffice
                for (Data param : parameters.parameters) {
                    query.addParameter(serializationService.toObject(param));
                }

